text:
(1)
Seventh Ave., at and adjoining the N.W. corner of West 12th Street. Also shown is West 12th Street, north side, west from Seventh Ave., to and including Greenwich Ave. Buildings in the foreground, are 3-story frame houses. Nos. 20-22 Seventh Ave.
July 10, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, at a later date, showing the row of houses as they extend to West 13th Street, under demolition by house wreckers.
May 7, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
title: Manhattan: 7th Avenue - 12th Street (West) - [Rhinelander Row.]
